                  Entered, W.<interp inst="t17980418-1-person56" type="given" value="Entered"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17980418-1-person56" type="gender" value="indeterminate"></interp>
                  </persName>
             Wade.</p>
               <p>The prisoner did not say any thing in her defence, but called 
               <persName id="t17980418-1-person57">
                  Daniel
                   Ingram
               <interp inst="t17980418-1-person57" type="surname" value="Ingram"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17980418-1-person57" type="given" value="Daniel"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17980418-1-person57" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , a dealer in coals in Bream's-buildings, who had known her from 1793, and gave her an excellent character.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17980418-1-verdict6" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17980418-1-verdict6" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs> 
